{
  "text": "considerable overlap (57 \u00b1 27 nmol/L and 46 \u00b1 30 nmol/L, respectively). This observation, together with the decrease in 5-methylTHF concentration in whole-blood samples with low non-methyl folate, is consistent with a previous report showing that freezing and thawing resulted in a change in folate vitamer distribution from methyl to nonmethyl folate, albeit in samples from rats [CITATION_1] . We did not genotype individuals in the current study; however, it is likely that those classified as high non-methyl folate were of the T/T genotype for the 5,10-methenylTHF reductase C677T polymorphism. These results show a clear potential to misrepresent folate vitamer distribution in RBCs when stored whole-blood samples are not handled adequately. In contrast, WBL was considerably stable over a period of 4 h for all folate forms and should be considered for storage preferable to whole blood because the sample handling during thawing is less sensitive to changes in methyl and non-methyl folates.",
